<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>DutchNews.nl</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/</link><description>DutchNews.nl brings daily news from The Netherlands in English</description><lastBuildDate>Fri, 21 Jun 2024 07:58:29 +0000</lastBuildDate><item><title>A few days of summer ahead, before the rain returns</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/06/a-few-days-of-summer-ahead-before-the-rain-returns/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-237202 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-society category-weather"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> A few days of summer ahead, before the rain returns</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-06-21T07:58:29+00:00"> June 21, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-141794" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_141794"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="713" sizes="(max-width: 1018px) 100vw, 1018px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/beach-at-sunset.png" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/beach-at-sunset.png 1018w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/beach-at-sunset-560x392.png 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/beach-at-sunset-768x538.png 768w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/beach-at-sunset-640x448.png 640w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/beach-at-sunset-89x62.png 89w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/beach-at-sunset-130x91.png 130w" width="1018"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-141794"> Sunny skies ahead Photo: DutchNews.nl</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">The Netherlands is in for a short period of dry, warm, summer </span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">weather,</span><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> weather forecasters said on Friday.</span></p><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">While there may be a few showers on Saturday, the next five days at least will be dry with sunshine and temperatures in the mid to high 20s, the </span><a class="editor-rtfLink" href="https://www.knmi.nl/nederland-nu/weer/verwachtingen" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><span data-preserver-spaces="true">KNMI weather bureau said</span></a><span data-preserver-spaces="true">. The best of the sunshine </span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">is set</span><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> for midweek.</span></p><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">But by the end of next week, the rain, and possibly thunderstorms, could be back. And the first week of July </span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">is likely to</span><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> be </span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">cooler</span><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> with less sunshine. </span></p><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">Weather bureau </span><a class="editor-rtfLink" href="https://www.weeronline.nl/nieuws/21-6-2024-weekendweer" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><span data-preserver-spaces="true">Weeronline</span></a><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> paints a similar picture. “By Thursday, there is a good chance that we will leave the summery weather behind us,” according to weatherman Berend van Straaten.</span></p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/society/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/weather/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=237202</guid><pubDate>Fri, 21 Jun 2024 07:58:29 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Benefit agency often negligent in checking ability to work</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/06/benefit-agency-often-negligent-in-checking-ability-to-work/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-237200 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-accidents category-jobs category-society"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Benefit agency often negligent in checking ability to work</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-06-21T07:49:04+00:00"> June 21, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-181144" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_181144"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="480" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/IMG_7349.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/IMG_7349.jpg 640w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/IMG_7349-560x420.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/IMG_7349-83x62.jpg 83w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/IMG_7349-130x98.jpg 130w" width="640"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-181144"> Photo: DutchNews.nl</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">Many people who are unfit to work through illness or disability are not being properly assessed by officials from the </span><a class="editor-rtfLink" href="https://www.ad.nl/binnenland/beoordeling-arbeidsongeschiktheid-uwv-onder-de-maat-dit-gaat-echt-alle-perken-te-buiten~a6e7f91b/" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><span data-preserver-spaces="true">UWV, the AD</span></a><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> reported on Friday, quoting the benefits agency’s </span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">own</span><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> research.</span></p><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">In more than half the cases, the research was not carried out properly, medical records were not accessed or the wrong conclusions were reached about how much work people could do, the AD said. </span></p><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">The agency research is based on a random selection of 239 files as part of annual quality controls.<br/> </span></p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">The benefits agency is supposed to calculate how much work people </span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">are able to</span><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> do, and their benefits are based on this figure.<br/> </span></p><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">The problem is particularly acute in follow-up telephone assessments, which are often used to check up on claimants after several months, the paper said. Some 80% of these checks were not done properly.</span></p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/accidents/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/jobs/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/society/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=237200</guid><pubDate>Fri, 21 Jun 2024 07:49:04 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Elderly tourist found alive in Spain after night in the open</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/06/elderly-tourist-found-alive-in-spain-after-night-in-the-open/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-237191 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-dutch-european-news category-tourism"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Elderly tourist found alive in Spain after night in the open</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-06-21T07:30:27+00:00"> June 21, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-230041" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_230041"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="1697" sizes="(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Depositphotos_71403569_XL-scaled.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Depositphotos_71403569_XL-scaled.jpg 2560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Depositphotos_71403569_XL-560x371.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Depositphotos_71403569_XL-1200x796.jpg 1200w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Depositphotos_71403569_XL-360x240.jpg 360w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Depositphotos_71403569_XL-768x509.jpg 768w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Depositphotos_71403569_XL-1536x1018.jpg 1536w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Depositphotos_71403569_XL-2048x1358.jpg 2048w" width="2560"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-230041"> Photo: Depositphotos.com</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>A 75-year-old Dutch tourist who went missing in a mountainous area in southern Spain on Wednesday has been found alive, local Spanish <a href="https://www.axarquiaplus.es/rescatan-a-un-anciano-holandes-con-alzheimer-en-murcia-tras-perderse-en-un-viaje-de-alicante-a-malaga/">media</a> reported.</p><p>The man, who suffers from Alzheimer’s disease, was on a journey from Alicante to Malaga with his family and had stopped at a local look-out point in the Ricote Valley in Murcia when he wandered off.</p><p>Rescue workers mounted an intensive search but only found him after drone footage showed the man walking around aimlessly the next day. He was exhausted, Gurdia Civil officers said, but otherwise unhurt.</p><p>The case is the last in a spate of incidents involving missing tourists. Several tourists have <a href="https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/06/dutch-tourist-found-dead-in-car-in-crete/">died</a> from heat-related incidents in Greece and some are still missing.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/dutch-european-news/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/tourism/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=237191</guid><pubDate>Fri, 21 Jun 2024 07:30:27 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Hanneke Sanou]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Bunq says it will compensate victims of online banking scams</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/06/bunq-says-it-will-compensate-victims-of-online-banking-scams/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-237194 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-banking category-crime category-fraud category-society"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Bunq says it will compensate victims of online banking scams</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-06-21T07:28:27+00:00"> June 21, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-163916" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_163916"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="500" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/bunq-phone.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/bunq-phone.jpg 600w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/bunq-phone-560x467.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/bunq-phone-74x62.jpg 74w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/bunq-phone-130x108.jpg 130w" width="600"/></figure><main class="px-4"><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">Online bank Bunq has told account holders that it will compensate them if they become victims of a banking scam. </span></p><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">Bunq said </span><a class="editor-rtfLink" href="https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/06/online-bank-bunq-steps-up-security-after-scam-claims/" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><span data-preserver-spaces="true">earlier this month</span></a><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> it had upped security measures after an investigation by broadcaster NOS and the NRC newspaper found dozens of people had lost millions of euros to scammers from their Bunq accounts. </span></p><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">Now Bunq said that victims will get up to 100% of their losses refunded. “We will assess each case individually according to the principle ‘compensate damage in full unless’,” Bunq said. “We are going beyond the </span><a class="editor-rtfLink" href="https://www.nvb.nl/media/5661/criteria-for-awarding-compensation-for-loss-arising-from-bank-help-desk-scams-spoofing-june-2nd-2021.pdf" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><span data-preserver-spaces="true">criteria established</span></a><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> by the Dutch banking association NVB and in distressing cases we may be extra lenient.”</span></p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">Bunq pointed out earlier this month that of the 10,000 cases of bank helpdesk fraud reported to the NVB, just 85 involved Bunq accounts.</span></p><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">The decision follows criticism of the bank by finance minister Steven van Weyenberg, who described comments by Bunq chief executive Ali Niknam as ‘</span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">totally</span><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> inappropriate”. Niknam said Bunq account holders who had been conned had effectively “given their car keys away” by passing their inlog codes to thieves. </span></p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/banking/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/crime/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/fraud/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/society/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=237194</guid><pubDate>Fri, 21 Jun 2024 07:28:27 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Police warn about capacity surrounding next year’s Nato summit</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/06/police-warn-about-capacity-surrounding-next-years-nato-summit/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-237189 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-foreign-affairs category-nato category-police category-the-hague"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Police warn about capacity surrounding next year’s Nato summit</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-06-21T07:07:17+00:00"> June 21, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-227530" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_227530"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="1333" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Depositphotos_497136744_L.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Depositphotos_497136744_L.jpg 2000w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Depositphotos_497136744_L-560x373.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Depositphotos_497136744_L-1200x800.jpg 1200w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Depositphotos_497136744_L-360x240.jpg 360w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Depositphotos_497136744_L-768x512.jpg 768w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Depositphotos_497136744_L-1536x1024.jpg 1536w" width="2000"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-227530"> Photo: Depositphotos</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>Dutch police chiefs have written to the country’s mayors urging them not to approve any events for three days in July next year – because the Netherlands is hosting the Nato summit.</p><p>The three-day event from July 24 to July 26 will require so much police capacity that there will be no-one left to deal with other events, police chiefs say. Police leave during the period is also likely to be restricted.</p><p>Preparations for the summit have already begun. “We don’t just need more capacity during the summit,” police chief Willem Woelders said. “It will be needed before the summit, in connection with the build-up. In addition, some of the work done by police officers deployed at the summit itself will have to be picked up by others.”</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>In total, 150 ministers and 6,000 delegation members will come to the Netherlands for the event and will also need to be escorted from the airport to their hotel, and to and from the summit venue.</p><p>“This will be the largest security operation ever to take place in the Netherlands,” Woelders said. “Everyone is going to notice it.”</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/foreign-affairs/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/nato/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/police/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/the-hague/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=237189</guid><pubDate>Fri, 21 Jun 2024 07:07:17 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Health insurers tear up contracts with private GP firm</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/06/health-insurers-tear-up-contracts-with-private-gp-firm/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-237181 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-business category-health category-insurance newsletter-include"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Health insurers tear up contracts with private GP firm</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-06-20T14:13:12+00:00"> June 20, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-228828" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_228828"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="576" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Depositphotos_18388775_S.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Depositphotos_18388775_S.jpg 1000w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Depositphotos_18388775_S-560x323.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Depositphotos_18388775_S-768x442.jpg 768w" width="1000"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-228828"> Photo: Depositphotos.com</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>The big four health insurers have torn up their contracts with private family doctors’ company Co-Med and are now looking for alternative options for their 50,000 clients.</p><p>On Wednesday CZ, VGZ, Menzis and Zilveren Kruis accused the company of failing to meet its obligations after a string of complaints from patients about access and the availability of qualified staff.</p><p>“We have come to the conclusion that Co-Med cannot guarantee the provision of good healthcare,” <a href="https://www.dutchnews.nl/wpcms/wp-admin/post.php?post=237181&amp;action=edit">CZ said in a statement</a>.</p><p>By cancelling the contracts, the insurers will no longer pay people to be treated in one of the 13 Co-Med family doctor practices it runs nationwide.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>Patients who are considered to be the most vulnerable will be priority placements with a new family doctor but there needs to be a “structural solution” for all the patients who are written in at a Co-Med practice, the health insurers said.</p><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">Co-Med has been trying to build up a position in the Dutch healthcare market. It was launched in 2019 by three Limburg businessmen, who said at the time the aim was to relieve doctors of their support tasks, such as roster planning and bookkeeping.</span></p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Incontent"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_incontent" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Incontent"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_incontent-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">The company now owns 13 family doctor clinics, many of which were bought from doctors who were retiring and had not been able to find someone to take over their practices. The company works largely with freelance doctors who are responsible for some 50,000 patients in Breda, Zwolle, Amsterdam, Eindhoven </span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">and</span><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> Enschede. </span></p><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">However, its operations have been hit by a string of complaints about accessibility, poor care </span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">and</span><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> the use of unqualified staff. Health ministry inspectors have also ordered the company to “improve the availability and accessibility of care”, saying Co-Med has shown “</span><a class="editor-rtfLink" href="https://www.igj.nl/actueel/nieuws/2024/04/17/aanwijzing-co-med" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><span data-preserver-spaces="true">serious shortcomings</span></a><span data-preserver-spaces="true">”. </span></p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/business/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/health/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/insurance/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=237181</guid><pubDate>Thu, 20 Jun 2024 14:13:12 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Three arrested for fraud involving Groningen gas grants</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/06/three-arrested-for-fraud-involving-groningen-gas-grants/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-237177 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-crime category-groningen-gas category-society newsletter-include"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Three arrested for fraud involving Groningen gas grants</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-06-20T13:49:51+00:00"> June 20, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-57570" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_57570"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="284" sizes="(max-width: 498px) 100vw, 498px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/groningen-earthquake-damage.png" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/groningen-earthquake-damage.png 498w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/groningen-earthquake-damage-300x171.png 300w" width="498"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-57570"> Earthquakes in the north have damaged houses. Photo: Depositphotos.com</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">Two men and one woman from Groningen have been arrested for fraud involving money that should have been spent on repairing damage caused to property by earthquakes in the region.</span></p><p>In total, the three are said to have made 50 fraudulent applications for grants, <span data-preserver-spaces="true">totalling</span><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> €350,000. Of that €200,000 has already been received.<br/> </span><br/> <span data-preserver-spaces="true">Three homes in the province were searched by police who took away paperwork, computers </span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">and</span><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> telephones, tax officials said. The homes and bank accounts of the three suspects were also sequestered.</span></p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">The investigation began after an alert from two government agencies set up to facilitate the payment of funding to repair earthquake damage.</span></p><p>“The two men submitted applications for several houses and the 27-year-old suspect’s construction company was said to have done the repair work for the homes,” <a href="https://www.rtvnoord.nl/misdaad/1178521/fiod-houdt-drie-groningers-aan-voor-fraude-met-bevingsschades-update">RTV Noord</a> quoted official documents as saying.</p><p>“However, investigations revealed that the damage had not been repaired and the invoices submitted were falsified. In addition, the pair had claimed additional money for several other properties they owned using false documents.”</p><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">All three are being held in custody while the investigation continues.<br/> </span></p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Incontent"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_incontent" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Incontent"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_incontent-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>Since the Slochteren gas field was opened in 1963 the Dutch state has earned €360 billion from gas extraction, with another €66 billion split between energy giants Shell and ExxonMobil.</p><p>But the cost to the community was high: more than 1,600 earthquakes have hit the region since the 1980s, damaging 85,000 buildings. The turning point was a quake measuring 3.6 on the Richter scale in the village of Huizinge in 2012.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/crime/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/groningen-gas/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/society/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=237177</guid><pubDate>Thu, 20 Jun 2024 13:49:51 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Vaccination rate for babies is stable, but down for children</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/06/vaccination-rate-for-babies-is-stable-but-down-for-children/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-237175 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-health category-society category-vaccinations newsletter-include"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Vaccination rate for babies is stable, but down for children</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-06-20T13:26:53+00:00"> June 20, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-143057" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_143057"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="427" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/child-vaccination-.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/child-vaccination-.jpg 640w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/child-vaccination--360x240.jpg 360w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/child-vaccination--560x374.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/child-vaccination--92x62.jpg 92w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/child-vaccination--130x87.jpg 130w" width="640"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-143057"> Photo: SELF Magazine</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>The vaccination rate among children over the age of nine continues to fall, and the trend is worrying, <a href="https://www.rivm.nl/en/news/vaccination-coverage-of-babies-and-toddlers-remained-about-same">public health institute RIVM</a> said on Thursday.</p><p>The number of children vaccinated for diphtheria, tetanus and polio by the age of nine has gone down from 81.1% to 78.2.% and the take-up rate for the MMR jab for mumps, measles, and rubella has gone down by a similar amount to 78.5%, the RIVM said.</p><p>Rotterdam has the lowest vaccination rate of the four big cities. Nationwide, 83.1% of babies have had all the basic vaccinations but in Rotterdam the figure is just 74.6%. Just 62% of children are fully vaccinated in the port city by the age of nine.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>But there has been no further decline in the vaccination rate among babies since the RIVM sounded the alarm last year, the government agency said.</p><p>In fact coverage for the MMR vaccination (mumps, measles and rubella) and for the vaccination against meningococcal disease types A, C, W and Y may even have increased.</p><p>The World Health Organisation considers 90% to be safe, but the RIVM takes 95% as its target.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/health/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/society/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/vaccinations/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=237175</guid><pubDate>Thu, 20 Jun 2024 13:26:53 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Romania says yes, clearing the way for Mark Rutte to head Nato</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/06/romania-says-yes-clearing-the-way-for-mark-rutte-to-head-nato/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-237168 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-foreign-affairs category-nato newsletter-top-article"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Romania says yes, clearing the way for Mark Rutte to head Nato</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-06-20T13:13:03+00:00"> June 20, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-237172" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_237172"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="667" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Depositphotos_688747654_S.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Depositphotos_688747654_S.jpg 1000w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Depositphotos_688747654_S-560x374.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Depositphotos_688747654_S-360x240.jpg 360w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Depositphotos_688747654_S-768x512.jpg 768w" width="1000"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-237172"> Mark Rutte at a Nato summit in Lithuania last year. Photo: Depositphotos.com</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>Outgoing Dutch prime minister Mark Rutte is now set to take over as secretary general of Nato, following the withdrawal of Romania’s candidate Klaus Iohannis.</p><p>Iohannis told a <a href="https://www.presidency.ro/ro/media/sedinta-consiliului-suprem-de-aparare-a-tarii1718883520">press conference</a> on Thursday that he was pulling out of the race, removing the last obstacle to Rutte’s appointment. Nato ambassadors are expected to formally announce the move next week.</p><p>There is no formal procedure for naming the secretary general but all 32 members must agree. Earlier this week both <a href="https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/06/hungary-backs-dutch-prime-minister-mark-rutte-for-top-nato-job/">Slovakia and Hungary</a> said they had no objections. Rutte had been the US favoured choice for months.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>Rutte will be the fourth Dutch leader of Nato, following Dirk Stikker (1961-1964), Joseph Luns (1971-1984) and Jaap de Hoop Scheffer (2004-2009).</p><p>Outgoing secretary general Jens Stoltenberg <a href="https://www.nato.int/cps/en/natohq/opinions_226837.htm?selectedLocale=en">told a meeting</a> in Canada on Wednesday that Rutte is a “great man” who “strongly believes in the transatlantic bond”.</p><p>“He’s a friend and colleague, Stoltenberg said. “So Nato will be very good hands, given that Mark Rutte is going to be the next secretary general.”</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/foreign-affairs/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/nato/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=237168</guid><pubDate>Thu, 20 Jun 2024 13:13:03 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Germany pulls plug on Tennet grid sale, citing financing issues</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/06/germany-pulls-plug-on-tennet-grid-sale-citing-financing-issues/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-237157 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-business category-energy"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Germany pulls plug on Tennet grid sale, citing financing issues</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-06-20T11:15:57+00:00"> June 20, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-206590" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_206590"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="1512" sizes="(max-width: 2016px) 100vw, 2016px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/IMG_1790.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/IMG_1790.jpg 2016w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/IMG_1790-560x420.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/IMG_1790-1200x900.jpg 1200w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/IMG_1790-768x576.jpg 768w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/IMG_1790-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/IMG_1790-640x480.jpg 640w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/IMG_1790-83x62.jpg 83w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/IMG_1790-130x98.jpg 130w" width="2016"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-206590"> Photo: DutchNews.nl</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>Dutch grid operator Tennet has failed in its efforts to sell its German operations to the German government, which has cited budgetary constraints as the reason the sale is not going ahead.</p><p>Tennet says it is now looking to other public or private options to finance the investment needed for the German grid arm.</p><p>Tennet, which is wholly owned by the Dutch government, acquired 11,000 kilometres of the German electricity grid from EON in 2011 and controls around 9,000 kilometres of the grid in the Netherlands.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>Caretaker finance minister Steven van Weyenberg told <a href="https://open.overheid.nl/documenten/c6275a39-fa24-498d-a629-1a4c9699bacc/file">MPs in a briefing</a> on Thursday that the collapse of the deal will hit the treasury to the tune of €1.6 billion in the short term and that money from the pending sale had already been incorporated into government spending plans.</p><p>Decisions will have to now be made about Tennet Germany’s future financing, Van Weyenberg said.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/business/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/energy/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=237157</guid><pubDate>Thu, 20 Jun 2024 11:15:57 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item></channel></rss>